title: For Sale:  The Bernardelli VP Vest Pocket Pistol
location: The Bernardelli VP Vest Pocket Pistol .25 acp, Orlando, Florida
postcontent:
1954 Bernardelli-Gardone V.T. Italia- Cal 6.35 BRE. VP (Vest Pocket). This is an older well made Italian Semi-Auto 25 ACP in Good Condition.  Gun functions perfectly and is a nice little piece for a collection.

Bernardelli enter into the gun business in 1631 first making barrels in Gardone Val Trompia, Brescia Italy. In 1865 Vincenzo Bernardelli founded the company which still exist today. In the 1920's Bernardelli also manufactured componets for Alfa Romeo aircraft engins. In the 1930's they made an Italian service revelover know as the System Bodeo, Model 1889. They are also know for crafting very high-end shotguns. After World War II, Bernardelli introduced its first self-loading pistol, the VP (Vest Pocket) Model, which was based on the Walther Model 9.

The Bernardelli VP is a very small blowback-operated striker-fired .25 caliber (6.35 mm) pistol with a barbell-shaped takedown latch at the rear. It has a full length slide that covers the 2" barrel, with an external extractor on the right side, an internal connector on the left side; a 5 shot magazine that incorporates a magazine safety.

For sale $500 obo

title: For Sale/Trade:  800 Rounds Federal HST .40S&W JHP
postcontent:
Best CCW Ammo you can buy!

For sale/trade is 800 rounds of Federal HST 155gr JHP for a .40S&W. Current retail price on this is between $1.25/round and $1.50/round - I am asking far less than that for cash offers.

Federal released its Hydra-Shok line of ammunition to capture the law enforcement market years ago, and while it was a good round - it proved troublesome when going through barriers before reaching its target - clogging much of the time.

Federal corrected the problem by introducing a line known as HST, and it was tested extensively by the FBI upon its release in .40 caliber, and adopted as their ammunition after blowing the tests out of the water. This is currently the only ammunition I will carry as I feel like it is the only ammunition to hold a candle to the famous "Black Talon".

It's easy to find the much less desirable Hydra-Shok ammunition on the shelf, and many people are intrigued by the "post" inside the hollow point. If you do the research, and I suggest you do, you will find that HST is extremely tough to beat.

That's why HST has almost never (in my experience) been for sale on the shelves at your local gun shop - I have only ever found it online, for a premium price, and in small or limited quantities. I have recently switched to a different caliber for my preferred CCW and cannot find anywhere that sells HST in bulk, must less a place with a single box in stock right now.

I live in Puyallup, but will be willing to drive a reasonable distance to meet - or even ship if you want to pay for shipping.

Take a look here for FBI Protocol test results on this ammunition
http://le.atk.com/ammunition/federal/handgun/details.aspx?id=567

title: For Sale:  8mm Mauser Zf-39 sniper rifle, built on a Bruno 98k rifle, C&R
postcontent:
Mauser 98K vintage sniper rifle build in 8mm Mauser (8x57).  Rifle was built on a peened 1943 DOU (Bruno (Waffen-Werke Brünn AG,Waffenwerke Bruenn, Bystrica, Czechoslovakia)) for vintage sniper rifle competition by a professional gunsmith.  

This rifle is a Russian capture rifle and was initially part of a crate purchased for reenacting and was used for that purpose for several years.  Eventually I had the barrel, stock and handguard replaced with ones that were in better shape for use in Vintage Military rifle matches.  I later had the rifle converted to a sniper rifle for use in Vintage Sniper Rifle matches with the addition of a reproduction ZF-39 scope and solid ring high turret mounts, at that time the entire rifle was polished and re-blued.  

The reproduction Zf-39 scope is 4x magnification and has post and crosshair reticle and is legal for Vintage Sniper Rifle matches.  The scopes objective and ocular both unscrew in order to mount in the solid high turret mounts. The high turret mount scope and rings are removable, the bases are both screwed and soldered into place, as per original specifications. The scope has not been soldered in place in the rings as the originals were and should be soldered into place at some point.  

The peened markings on the receiver are covered up by the scope mounts.  The stock that is currently on it is also a Russian capture stock that has been filled with some type of resin near the butt plate. There are some original markings on the replacement barrel and butt plate.  MOST of the part numbers match, the bolt does not match. This is a complete, all original, 100% Colt AR-15 A2 upper of mid-80s vintage in EXCELLENT condition. It features a 1/7 twist Colt Gov't profile barrel and everything is near perfect on it. The upper is paired to a new Aero Precision mil-spec lower using many of the Colt lower receiver parts. The stock is a Colt USGI A2 stock with Colt rifle buffer and spring. As you can see by the photos there is little to no wear on the upper receiver and the lower is new. Unfortunately the lower is darker than the mid-80s gray color Colt used on the upper. It has the 1/7 twist, government profile barrel with the deadly bayonet lug (the barrel is a smaller diameter under the handguards). It has all the A2 features including 800M sights, forward assist, brass deflector, etc.

The sale will include one Colt-brand Colorado neutered and legal, non-high capacity, non-massacre capable magazine which is clearly incapable of causing destruction and mayhem on a large scale. So you can feel very socially responsible when you purchase this gun/magazine combo.

I fired 10 rounds of 69gr SMK ammo for function and, naturally, it functioned perfectly. USGI and Magpul mags fit the lower without issue.
